        <Parent_String>presses (cupboards) [300039252], cupboards (case furniture) [300039183], case furniture [300038860], storage and display furniture [300164528], furniture by form or function [300048628], furniture [300037680], furnishings by form or function [300037342], furnishings (works) [300037336], Furnishings (hierarchy name) [300037335], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Large, but fairly low, cupboards with both the upper and lower sections containing enclosed storage space; of a type made in 16th- and 17th-century England and 17th-century America. Distinct from "court cupboards" which have an enclosed storage cabinet above and an open shelf or shelves below.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aparadores grandes, pero medianamente bajos con ambas secciones, inferior y superior, con áreas de almacenaje; de un tipo fabricado en los siglos XVI y XVII en Inglaterra y en el siglo XVII en América. Se diferencian de "court cupboard" que tiene un gabinete de almacenamiento cerrado arriba y una repisa o repisas abiertas debajo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Grote, maar tamelijk lage wandkasten met een afgesloten opbergruimte in het boven- en ondergedeelte. Dit type werd gemaakt in de 16e en 17e eeuw in Engeland en in de 17e eeuw in Amerika. Te onderscheiden van '@court cupboards', waarbij het bovengedeelte een afgesloten opbergkast en het ondergedeelte een of meerdere open planken heeft.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>上下密閉儲藏空間的大型矮櫃，製造於十六和十七世紀的英格蘭與十七世紀的美國。與「低碗櫃」不同，「低碗櫃」上面有櫥櫃，下方則是開放式層架。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
